verflow (http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/laravel).\r\n\r\nIf you would like to propose new Laravel features, please make a pull request, or open an issue at https://github.com/laravel/internals/issues.\r\n-->\r\n\r\n- Laravel Version: 5.6.9\r\n- PHP Version: 7.1.7\r\n- Database Driver & Version: MySQL 5.7.19\r\n\r\n### Description:\r\nWhen invoking a method which is named like an \"accessor/getter\" through string interpolation, it will trigger the `__get` magic function resulting to unexpected method behavior.\r\n\r\n### Steps To Reproduce:\r\n\r\n1. Create two models.\r\n    SampleModel.php, SampleRelatedModel.php\r\n\r\n2. Create relationship in SampleModel.php\r\n\r\n    ```\r\n    public function relatedModels()\r\n    {\r\n        return $this->hasMany(SampleRelatedModel::class);\r\n    }\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n3. Create an \"accessor-like\" method for relatedModels in SampleModel.php\r\n\r\n    ```\r\n    public function getRelatedModels()\r\n    {\r\n        return \"Sample Method\";\r\n    }\r\n    ```\r\n\r\n4. Test the methods\r\n\r\n- Call `$sampleModel->relatedModels;`. This will return a collection of `SampleRelatedModel`s related to it.\r\n\r\n- Call `$sampleModel->getRelatedModels()`. This will return `\"Sample Method\"` string.\r\n\r\n- Now, interpolate the previous call. `\"$sampleModel->getRelatedModels()\"`.\r\n  - This will cause an error saying: method `getRelatedModels` should return a relationship.\r\n\r\nI've traced the method calls, it seems to me that the interpolated call triggered the magic `__get` method of the model.\r\n\r\nThis is the result of what I've traced.\r\n\r\n```\r\n// Model.php\r\npublic function __get($key)\r\n{\r\n    return $this->getAttribute($key);\r\n}\r\n// |\r\n// V\r\n// HasAttributes.php\r\npublic function getAttribute($key)\r\n{\r\n    ...\r\n    return $this->getRelationValue($key);\r\n}\r\n// |\r\n// V\r\n// HasAttributes.php\r\npublic function getRelationValue($key)\r\n{\r\n    ...\r\n    if (method_exists($this, $key)) {\r\n        return $this->getRelationshipFromMethod($key);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n// |\r\n// V\r\n// HasAttributes.php\r\nprotected function getRelationshipFromMethod($method)\r\n{\r\n    $relation = $this->$method(); // <-- lastly to this\r\n    // $method = \"getRelatedModels\"\r\n    if (! $relation instanceof Relation) {\r\n        throw new LogicException(sprintf(\r\n            '%s::%s must return a relationship instance.', static::class, $method\r\n        ));\r\n    }\r\n    ...\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if this bug is PHP-specific or Laravel-specific. The bug was discussed here: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/49378402/laravel-type-error-too-few-arguments-to-function-app-productgettax-0-pa/49379823#49379823","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23636","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23636/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23636/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23636/events","html_url":"https://github.com/laravel/framework/issues/23636","id":306956816,"number":23636,"title":"Does not assign a foreign name.","user":{"login":"DmitrySkibitsky","id":20288556,"avatar_url":"https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/20288556?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky","html_url":"https://github.com/DmitrySkibitsky","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/DmitrySkibitsky/orgs","repos