 'min', 'max', 'rad2deg', 'round', 'sin', 'sinh',\r\n'sqrt', 'tan', 'tanh', 'base_convert', 'bindec', 'decbin', 'dechex', 'decoct', 'hexdec', 'octdec',]\r\n\r\n// E.g.:\r\n$number = new SuperNumber(64);\r\n$number->sqrt(); // Returns 8.\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt also supports some additional functions, like add(), subtract(), multiply(), divide(), mod(), format() which is an alias for number_format, as well as a custom mutator to do whatever you want to the current value with a callable function.\r\n\r\nI plan on adding more useful stuff.\r\n\r\nAnd they're also chainable, which will look excellent in views for quick calculations.\r\n\r\nThis is a real world example from one of the apps that I'm working on.\r\n\r\nI turned this:\r\n\r\n`number_format($nextBonus->points - user()->pointsEarned, 0)`\r\n\r\nInto this:\r\n\r\n`$nextBonus->points->sub(user()->pointsEarned)->format()`\r\n\r\nAnd this:\r\n\r\n`number_format(user()->pointsEarned / $nextBonus->points * 100, 0)`\r\n\r\nInto this:\r\n\r\n`user()->pointsEarned->percentOf($nextBonus->points)`\r\n\r\nSimply by initializing the SuperNumber class via the models' attribute getters.\r\n\r\n```\r\nclass User extends Model\r\n{\r\n    // ...\r\n\r\n    public function getPointsEarnedAttribute ($value) {\r\n        return new SuperNumber((int) $value);\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n--\r\n\r\nI think this will be a great addition to Laravel's `$casts` model functionality, so I was thinking to create a pull request with this new class to be applied on a new casting type. But first, I'd like to see what you guys think of the idea. Maybe it's simply too much for just some silly numbers? Maybe it'll add to the load time?\r\n\r\nI'd love to hear your oppinions on this.","score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23574","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/laravel/framework/issues/23574/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https